{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThe single `state[\"signature\"]` slot is last-writer-wins, so one kind clobbers another.\nThis is the root-cause fix and the riskiest slice (back-compat + compaction), done first.\n## What\nReplace the slot with `state[\"attestations\"]`, a kind-keyed map applied per-key-LWW like\n`process_workflow_run`. `process_signature` routes by `data[\"kind\"]` (fallback: parse\n`manifest[0]`). New code writes ONLY `attestations` into compiled state and never writes\n`state[\"signature\"]` into events. Read fold-in: a ticket/snapshot carrying only the legacy\n`signature` is folded into `attestations` on read (kind from its manifest). SNAPSHOT mirror\n(expand phase): a NEW snapshot ALSO synthesizes a legacy `signature` (= most-recent\nattestation) so old/rolled-back clones can still read it; a named cutover release drops it.\n## Scope\n`src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py` (`process_signature`, `process_snapshot` fold-in +\nmirror), `src/rebar/_commands/compact.py` (synthesize mirror in SNAPSHOT), `ticket_state.schema.json`.\nNo change to the signed payload.\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `attestations` map replaces the single slot; additive across kinds, replace within a kind.\n- [ ] Routing by `data[\"kind\"]`; `manifest[0]` fallback for legacy events.\n- [ ] New code never writes `state[\"signature\"]` into events; legacy single `signature` folded into `attestations` on read.\n- [ ] New SNAPSHOTs synthesize a legacy `signature` mirror (most-recent attestation); cutover release to drop it is named in a comment/doc.\n- [ ] Compaction/SNAPSHOT round-trips all kinds; empty map omitted from `show`/state."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782783720245535001,"uuid":"0ec78264-1ad0-44b0-b2f4-916ad7a5907e"}